CARD::uJObZafd.label: PV Infeed Explanation
CARD::uJObZafd.text: In this demo, the potential and actual infeed are the same because all infeed is fed into the grid. In the future, the community controller will also be able to adjust the infeed.

CARD::A1OJJKxf.text: • Shifted Power: When the power demand cannot be met (e.g., when there is no PV infeed present), the demand shifts in terms of energy. A higher power value is configured to catch up with past demand.

CARD::ygXTU4WD.text: • Actual Power: The community control algorithm allows power to be used only for charging e-cars, and only available PV power can be used for this purpose.

CARD::qUSCUlar.label: Charing Station Explanation
CARD::qUSCUlar.text: • Power Demand: The current power needed by the charging station for the connected car.
